# Trivy ignore file — list CVE IDs (one per line) to suppress from scan results.
# Only suppress a CVE here if it has been reviewed and accepted as a known risk
# (e.g. not exploitable in this context, or no fix available upstream).
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# Example (remove the leading # to suppress):
# CVE-2024-12345
